    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - Appendix B - Torques - Torque Guidelines</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s265appb.1">
        <title>Torque Guidelines</title>
        <svcproc id="s265appb.1.1" svcproctype="torque" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not substitute fasteners. Original equipment standard hardware is
                        defined as Class 10.9 metric or Grade 8 standard coarse thread bolts and nuts and hardened flat
                        washers (Rockwell "C" 38-45), all phosphate coated.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>The standard torque charts provide the tightening torque for general application of standard hardware
                listed in the Parts Catalog for original equipment.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect parts for cleanliness and defects before assembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
